The Telugu Desam Party has announced an assistance of Rs. 5 lakh to the family of Hyderabad Central University student Vemula Rohith who committed suicide recently.A delegation of the TDP comprising Ministers Ravela Kishore Babu and P. Sujatha, TDP AP unit president K. Kala Venkata Rao and senior leader M. Narsimhulu called on the members of the bereaved family here. Expressing deep regrets at the incident, the delegation assured a teaching job to Rahotâ€™s brother based on his qualifications and a job to his mother in the same institution.Asserting that the TDP would stand by the family, the delegation wanted stringent action initiated against those found guilty after the fact-finding committee constituted by the Union government submitted its report.